# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# |<----  Using a maximum of 50 characters  ---->|

# Explain why this change is being made
# |<----   Try to limit each line to a maximum of 72 characters   ---->|

# Provide links or keys to any relevant tickets, articles or other resources
# Example: Fixes #23

# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    refactor (refactoring production code)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    docs     (changes to documentation)
#    test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc)
#    perf     (performance improvements)
#    ci       (changes to CI configuration files and scripts)
#    build    (changes to build system or external dependencies)
#    revert   (reverts a previous commit)
# --------------------
# Scope is optional and can be anything specifying the place of the commit change.
# For example: crawler, downloader, trainer, api, ci, etc.
# --------------------
# Subject should use imperative tone and say what you did.
# For example: "add feature" not "added feature" or "adds feature"
# --------------------
# Body should explain the motivation for the change and how it differs from
# previous behavior. This commit message should be able to answer "why?".
# --------------------
# Footer should contain any BREAKING CHANGES and reference any issues/tickets.
# Breaking changes should start with BREAKING CHANGE: and have space or two
# newlines before the footer message.
# --------------------
# Examples:
#
# feat(crawler): add rate limiting for GitHub API
#
# The crawler now respects GitHub's rate limits by implementing
# exponential backoff and request throttling.
#
# Fixes #42
# --------------------
# fix(trainer): resolve CUDA out of memory error
#
# Reduced batch size and implemented gradient accumulation
# to fix OOM errors on RTX 5090 with large models.
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: Batch size reduced from 8 to 4
# --------------------
